<P>
   &QL; 
MONTINI-COLUMN _ (Phoenix) Before reading it, remember, in order to
prevent brain freeze, take small sips. By EJ MONTINI. Story will
move in the ``A'' and ``K'' categories.
</P>
<P>
   SOLAR (Phoenix) _ Arizona has become the first state to order
utilities to produce a certain percentage of their electricity from
solar sources, a move that puts it at the forefront of the
clean-energy movement and could revive Arizona's lagging solar
industry. The Corporation Commission on Wednesday unanimously
approved a measure that will require utilities and other
electricity providers to derive a portion of their product from
solar and other renewable resources. Although 27 other states have
such mandated portfolios, Arizona is the first to require that
solar energy make up a specific portion of the mix. By MAX JARMAN.
Story will move in the ``A'' and ``F'' categories.
</P>
<P>
   SPURCROSS (Cave Creek, Ariz.) _ Cave Creek taxpayers could be
asked to cover a $6 million shortfall in the $21 million price
owners are asking to prevent the development of Spur Cross Ranch.
Some Town Council members are questioning what they claim is a 40
percent hike in the cost landowners are asking for the 2,200-acre
environmental gem. On Monday, the Town Council will consider a plan
backed by Mayor Vincent Francia that would raise part of the $21
million through a $6 million property tax. The tax would require
the approval of Cave Creek voters in the Nov. 7 election. By JERRY
KAMMER. Story will move in the ``A'' category.
</P>
