<HEADLINE>
CASHING IN AN OVERDUE RAIN CHECK 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By E.J. MONTINI  
 c.2000 The Arizona Republic  
(PHOENIX) - Writer's note: Most of what follows was written on
March 6, a Monday, when the high tem perature was 52 degrees and we
got 1.53 inches of rain. The column was stored in the computer ice
chest and not published because there was other news to write about
that day. Besides, I figured it would be best to serve it up, like
a frosty beverage, on our first 100-degree day. Before you
continue, remember, in order to prevent brain freeze, take small
sips:
