<SLUG> BC-NY-GIULIANI-CANCER-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
GIULIANI IS TESTED FOR PROSTATE CANCER 
</HEADLINE>
   c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Mayor Rudolph Giuliani underwent tests for prostate
cancer during a three-hour unannounced visit to Mount Sinai Medical
Center hospital on Wednesday morning, officials familiar with
Giuliani's schedule said.
</P>
<P>
   Giuliani's advisers declined on Wednesday night to discuss the
reason for the visit, or the outcome of the tests. A spokesman at
Mount Sinai also declined to comment.
</P>
<P>
   However, a friend of Giuliani said the test was for prostate
cancer, and described it as more than a routine screening.
</P>
<P>
   The cable channel New York One reported on Wednesday night that
Giuliani, who is 55, had gone last week for a routine prostate
cancer screening, and had asked to return for a second round of
testing because of an anomaly discovered in the tests.
</P>
<P>
   Giuliani's father, Harold, suffered from prostate cancer, which
led to his death in 1981.
</P>
<P>
   Giuliani has publicly counseled middle-aged men to undergo
annual visits for the exam.
</P>
</TEXT>
