   GERMANY-RUSSIA-LOOT (Moscow) _ On artworks seized during the
World War II-era by German and Russian troops. By Celestine Bohlen.
</P>
<P>
   U.S.-HOLOCAUST-ART (Dateline to come) _ A French Jew has claimed
that his family owned works that are now in three U.S. museums. By
Alan Riding.
</P>
<P>
   GARLAND-BOOK-REVIEW (Undated) _ Lonely quests through hostile
territory provide the high-minded desperation that serves as
ballast for ``Get Happy,'' Gerald Clarke's scandal-seeking yet
curiously wan biography of Judy Garland. Reviewed by Janet Maslin.
</P>
<P>
   TV-WONDERLAND (Hollywood) _ Why the TV show folded after two
shows. By Bernard Weinraub.
</P>
