<HEADLINE>
WINE OF THE WEEK 

</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  (For release Friday, April 28) 
 
By MICHAEL LONSFORD 
c. 2000 Houston Chronicle 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   On this day in 1789, Fletcher Christian led the ``mutiny on the
Bounty,'' rebelling against the stern captain of the HMS Bounty,
Lt. William Bligh.
</P>
<P>
   Also on this day in 1758, the fifth president of the United
States was born in Virginia. James Monroe died July 4,1831. What
other two U.S. presidents died on Independence Day _ and the same
day, at that? &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   If you like high-quality California cabernet, but your wallet is
about to mutiny, then check out the 1996 Gallo-Sonoma ``Frei
Ranch'' Cabernet Sauvignon _ 4 1/2 stars _ a ``mini''-version of
the inestimable Gallo Estate Cabernet, one of California's best.
The Frei Ranch is rich but well-structured, and with a nice
``grip.'' Think heavy red meats or pastas with tomatoes and garlic.
Lots of garlic.
</P>
<P>
   The low-$20s price tag is more than reasonable for a wine of
this quality.
</P>
<P>
   Answer: John Adams and Thomas Jefferson both died July 4, 1826,
the 50th anniversary of the signing of the Declaration of
Independence.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
WINE RATING &QL; 
5 stars: Outstanding &QL; 
4 stars: Fine &QL; 
3 stars:Good &QL; 
2 stars: Fair &QL; 
1 star: Poor &QL; 
 &QL; 
XXXX END OF STORY XXXX &QL; 
$$$
</P>
</TEXT>
