<P>
   &UR; On Sunday, April 30, the 25th anniversary of the fall of
Saigon, The Boston Globe will publish a 20-page special Vietnam
retrospective. Included in the package, moving today in advance,
are: &LR;
</P>
<P>
   VIET-GREENWAY (Ho Chi Minh City) _ Today Vietnam is a country
again, not just a war, as the government is fond of saying. By
H.D.S. Greenway. 1800 words.
</P>
<P>
   w/
</P>
<P>
   VIET-DANANG (Da Nang) _ The north-south division is still
present even today in the minds of many Vietnamese. By H.D.S.
Greenway. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   w/
</P>
<P>
   VIET-HUE (Hue) _ Today Hue bears little resemblance to the dust,
cordite, and death-filled city in those long days and nights. PHOTO
</P>
<P>
   w/
</P>
<P>
   VIET-PHNOM (Phnom Penh) _ Today, Vietnamese political influence
vies with Thai commercial interest for dominance in Laos.
</P>
<P>
   w/
</P>
<P>
   VIET-HOCHIMINH (Ho Chi Minh City) _ When the helicopters
arrived, the wind from their rotors sent shredded secrets flying
into the city that was about to be abandoned.
</P>
<P>
   VIET-HALBERSTAM (Kent, Ohio) _ How a divisive, unwinnable war
and a deceptive government changed the nation. By David Halberstam.
(2 takes)
</P>
