   &UR; SPORTS &LR;  (``s'' code)
</P>
<P>
   VECSEY-COLUMN (New York) _ Sports column on Toronto and New
York, which find themselves linked in three sports this weekend:
the Blue Jays vs. the Yankees, the Maple Leafs vs. the New Jersey
Devils in the NHL playoffs, and the Raptors vs. the Knicks in the
NBA playoffs. By George Vecsey.
</P>
<P>
   BKN-KNICKS (New York) _ The Knicks' Wednesday-night Game 2
victory over Toronto gives them a commanding 2-0 lead in this
first-round, best-three-out-of-five series. By Selena Roberts.
</P>
<P>
   BKN-VETERANS (New York) _ The Knicks are a veteran team, which
is why they survived close calls in the first two games of their
series with Toronto and now seem a sure bet to take on another
veteran team _ the Miami Heat _ in the second round of the
playoffs. And if you look around the league, you'll see that it's
the veterans who are also winning other close playoff matchups. By
Mike Wise.
</P>
<P>
   BKN-TV-SPORTS (Undated) _ TV Sports column, focusing on coverage
of the NBA playoffs. By Richard Sandomir.
</P>
<P>
   HKN-DEVILS-LEAFS (Toronto) _ Devils vs. Toronto, 7 p.m., Game 1
of their second-round playoff series.
</P>
<P>
   BBN-METS-REDS (New York) _ Cincinnati at Mets, 1:10 p.m. By Judy
Battista.
</P>
<P>
   TEN-ROGUE-PRODIGY (Undated) _ Growing up in the projects of East
Las Vegas, Claudia Meza wasn't a tennis prodigy with guaranteed
court times. Instead, she wore black lipstick, flashed gang signs
and concealed knives and brass knuckles in her baggy pants. By Tom
Spousta.
</P>
<P>
   RUN-PENN-RELAYS (Philadelphia) _ First day of the Penn Relays.
</P>
