<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-GETAWAY-FESTIVALS26-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Southern happenings
 &HT;    By Paula Crouch Thrasher
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QR;  Pine Mountain, Ga. _ Callaway Gardens hosts ``Celebrate the
Arts! A Grand Celebration of Music and Art'' Saturday and Sunday,
with chamber music and performing arts programs led by pianist and
Newnan native Charles Wadsworth, a performance by LaGrange native
Fred Newman of ``Doug'' cartoon fame, and visual arts including
featured artist John Wilson. 1-800-225-5292,
www.callawaygardens.com.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Huntsville, Ala. _ Panoply, Friday through Sunday in Big
Spring International Park, features music on open-air stages, a
children's discovery area, a juried art show, a choreography
competition, a theater demo tent and a wide variety of food.
256-519-2787, www.panoply.org.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Destin, Fla. _ The 14th annual Sandestin Wine Festival
features more than 500 wines Thursday through Sunday at the
Sandestin Golf and Beach Resort. The main event is the Grand Wine
Tasting, at the Market Shops of Sandestin on Saturday and Sunday.
Tickets: 850-267-8092. Packages and reservations: 1-800-277-0800,
www.sandestin
</P>
<P>
   .com.
</P>
