u w BC-DAUGHTERS28-COX     04-27 0489
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-DAUGHTERS28-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    'DAUGHTERS TO WORK DAY' SPARKS DREAMS FOR MILLIONS, BACKERS SAY
 &HT;    By EMILY DEANS and BOB DEANS
 &HT;    c.2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ Eight years after the Ms. Foundation for Women
called for an annual Take Our Daughters to Work Day, the event has
given millions of young girls a glimpse of the American workplace.
</P>
<P>
   More than that, it has become a window into the widening choices
girls have in a society of increasing possibilities for women, said
Marie C. Wilson, president of the Ms. Foundation for Women.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's about America's daughters,'' she told about 150 women and
girls attending a White House ceremony to spotlight the annual
event. ``I want every girl in this country to know that you have
every right to grow up to be the president of the United States of
America or the secretary of the Treasury or to run a dot-com.''
</P>
<P>
   On Thursday, about 19 million girls journeyed to jobs across the
country, most with a mom or dad, Wilson estimated.
</P>
<P>
   While some educators have discouraged participation in the event
because it requires missing a day of school, its backers said it
has become a vital reminder of the broadening career horizons women
may pursue.
</P>
<P>
   ``It encourages girls to really be anything they wish to be, to
reinforce that beautiful voice that every girl has inside herself
that tells her 'You can do this,'' said Luz Borrero, executive
director of ``Cool Girls,'' an Atlanta organization that helps
low-income girls build a foundation for successful careers.
</P>
<P>
   ``Every girl needs that reinforcement, and I think this program
provides that opportunity,'' said Borrero, who attended the White
House event.
</P>
<P>
   Borrero said Atlanta businesses have embraced the annual day.
Atlanta companies such as the King &AMP; Spalding law firm, the UPS
parcel delivery service and Emory University took in 85 girls on
Thursday, she said, offering them mentoring programs and a day on
the job.
</P>
<P>
   Wilson also spoke up for stay-at-home moms, saying that women
who run households and raise children are creating ``social
capital.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Every time she cooks you a meal, every time she goes to a PTA
meeting,'' Wilson said, ``she's creating wealth.''
</P>
<P>
   Also speaking at the White House event was Treasury Secretary
Larry Summers, who brought along his twin 9-year-old daughters.
</P>
<P>
   President Clinton, who was traveling in Arkansas, sent a
prepared statement in support of Take Our Daughters to Work Day.
</P>
<P>
   ``Thanks to the courage and determination of women who blazed
new trails in our society, young women in America today have more
career opportunities open to them than ever before,'' Clinton
stated. ``Our daughters can look to a wide variety of inspiring
role models straight from today's headlines.''
</P>
<P>
   Bob Deans's e-mail address is bobdeans(at)coxnews.com
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
</P>
