   TEXAS-OLD HOTELS &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ They've housed presidents, film stars, royalty and
outlaws. Now, Texas' historic hotels are sparkling anew _ with all
their old charms intact. We show you 10 of our favorite historic
Texas hotels, from Austin's Driskill and Houston's Warwick to the
Hotel Paisano in Marfa, where James Dean and the cast stayed while
making ``Giant,'' and the Excelsior House Hotel in Jefferson, which
has hosted guests every night for almost 150 years. By PATRICIA
RODRIGUEZ. Story has moved in ``t'' travel category. (Accompanied
by OLD HOTELS-OTHERS.) &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
