<P>
   Moving in both International/Washington categories.
</P>
<P>
   IRS-GAO _ WASHINGTON _ More than two years after a Senate
hearing aired sensational charges of abuses by the Internal Revenue
Service, a congressional report says the most serious charges could
not be corroborated. The findings were somewhat embarrassing for
some Senate Republicans, who nevertheless emphsized that the agency
did have problems. (Malone, Cox News Service)
</P>
<P>
   DAUGHTERS _ WASHINGTON _ Eight years after the Ms. Foundation
called for an annual ``Take Your Daughters to Work Day,'' the event
has helped tens of millions
</P>
<P>
   of girls glimpse their future as career professionals. On
Thursday, an estimated 19 million more journeyed to jobs across the
country, most of them shadowing a mom or dad. ``It encourages girls
to really be anything they wish to be, to reinforce that beautiful
voice that every girl has inside herself that tells her 'You can do
this,'' said Luz Borrero, executive director of ``Cool Girls,'' and
Atlanta organization that helps low-income girls build a foundation
for successful careers. (Emily and Bob Deans, Cox News Service)
</P>
