   &UR; 25 YEARS LATER, CORRUPT CAPITALISM THRIVES IN VIETNAM &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; CORRUPT-VIETNAM-IHT-675&AMP;add &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   HO CHI MINH CITY _ There is a quiet discontent here 25 years
after victorious North Vietnamese troops swept into Saigon on April
29, 1975, driving the U.S.-backed South Vietnamese government from
power, sending thousands into re-education camps and installing
their own officials at every layer of the bureaucracy. It is a
largely hidden struggle in which people accept the need for
compromise, avoid political discussion, hustle for survival as
capitalists in a communist framework _ and reveal inner feelings
and complaints amid pleas for anonymity and furtive looks to see if
informants are listening...By Don Kirk, The International Herald
Tribune &QL;
</P>
