</P>
<P>
   &UR; SAIGON-PHOTO-TRUTH-INDEPENDENT &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   HO CHI MINH CITY _ One of the most celebrated photographs of the
Vietnam war, which gave the world so many haunting images, was
taken during the last few hours of April 29, 1975. It captured the
final chaotic moments before the American evacuation was complete.
Now, 25 years after the photograph was taken by UPI photographer
Hubert Van Es, it has emerged that the building in the picture was
not the U.S. Embassy but, in fact, an apartment block, some
distance away from the embassy compound. Most of the people in the
photograph were Vietnamese...By Fiona Bell, The Independent &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (TIMELY for this weekend's 25th anniv., Fall of Saigon!) &QL;
