   NEW YORK _ The saga of Elian Gonzalez, the six-year-old at the
center of a row between the U.S. and Cuba, has divided the boy's
family and reopened Miami's painful ethnic and political divisions.
But it has also divided the two cousins who rescued the boy,
leaving one as a temporary, publicity-hungry media star while the
other retreats bitterly back into the shadows...By Andrew Marshall,
The Independent &QL;
