Congressional hearings and television talk-show jibes about police
states that sanction the snatching of children at gunpoint. But in
the country at large, the forcible transfer of six-year-old Elian
Gonzalez from his Miami relatives to his father has been widely
applauded by ``regular folks,'' and Attorney General Janet Reno is
being hailed as a hero...By Mary Dejevsky, The Independent &QL;
