</P>
<P>
   DELHI _ India's most catastrophic drought for a century is
threatening the lives of 50 million people, as a cruel heat wave
scorches the bone-dry earth. This is the desperate face of India
that the ``green revolution,'' and a decade of good monsoons,
persuaded the world to believe was a thing of the past. Farmers
watch their milk cattle die; there is neither water nor food to
spare for them. The people, too, go hungry. Only the vultures are
glutted...By Peter Popham, The Independent &QL;
