the fear that other non-Communist countries in Southeast Asia would
topple like a row of dominoes seems farfetched. Yet what would have
happened if U.S. President Lyndon Johnson, faced with the awful
choice of opting in or out of Vietnam so early in his presidency,
had elected not to fight?...By Denis Warner, International Herald
Tribune &QL;
