</P>
<P>
   &UR; SURVIVOR-KILLINGFIELDS-IHT &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ Twenty-five years ago, on April 17, 1975, I was in
Phnom Penh, Cambodia. It was a city that had been under siege by
the Khmer Rouge for months, a place of fear and desperation. Our
family group of 16 left that night along with thousands of other
trying to get out of the city. This forced march was desperately
slow. It took us 10 days to get to Tonle Bati, usually reached from
Phnom Penh in an hour. This was just the beginning of the Killing
Fields...By Sichan Siv, International Herald Tribune) &QL;
