<P>
   &UR; DOT.COM-MOM-IHT &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   LONDON_ My daughter turned 3 when I signed on to be co-director
of an Internet start-up. She will shortly be 4. I have not seen
much of her fourth year. How do I calculate what I have earned? How
do I measure that I have lost? I have spent years writing and
reading about shareholder value. The new-economy guys have stock
options downloading into their dreams. But last week, I picked up
my 7-year-old son after school for the first time in a year.
Delight chased incredulity off his face. And that's when I knew
that my stock had finally gone up...By Avivah Wittenberg-Cox,
International Herald Tribune) &QL;
