<SLUG> BC-VIETNAM-ART-ADVISORY-NYT </SLUG>
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   On Sunday, April 30, the 25th anniversary of the fall of Saigon,
The Boston Globe will publish a 20-page special Vietnam
retrospective. Included in the package, moving today in advance,
are the following photos which have moved:
</P>
<P>
   (NYT2) HANOI, Vietnam -- April 27, 2000 -- ADV. FOR SUN, APRIL
30 -- VIETNAM-1-BOS -- The wing from a B-52 bomber in a pond in the
Ngoc Ha section of Hanoi in March.
</P>
<P>
   (NYT3) CU CHI, Vietnam -- April 27, 2000 -- ADV. FOR SUN., APRIL
30 -- VIETNAM-2-BOS -- A tourist from Taiwan emerging from the
150-mile network of tunnels in Cu Chi that the Viet Cong used to
wreak havoc on the US 25th Infantry Division headquartered there.
</P>
<P>
   (NYT4) HO CHI MINH CITY, Vietnam -- April 27, 2000 -- ADV. FOR
SUN., APRIL 30 -- VIETNAM-3-BOS -- Five-star hotels like the
Sofitel Plaza in Ho Chi Minh City, formerly Saigon, now cater to
Western businessmen and other foreign investors pushing Vietnam
toward a market economy. Dutch tourists look at the skyline from
the roof of the hotel.
</P>
<P>
   (NYT5) HANOI, Vietnam -- April 27, 2000 -- ADV. FOR SUN., APRIL
