announcement by Mayor Rudolph Giuliani Thursday that he has been
struck with prostate cancer presents him with a series of pressing
medical decisions in the two weeks ahead. But the confluence of
Giuliani's diagnoses and the state's political calendar could force
the mayor to make some pivotal decisions about his Senate candidacy
just as quickly, and over precisely the same difficult period of
