</P>
<P>
   (Center right)
</P>
<P>
   MAGAZINE-CLOSE (New York) _ Jack Kliger, the chief executive of
Hachette Filipacchi Magazines, announced Thursday that he would
close Mirabella, the women's magazine. In a speech to the staff and
in a statement, Kliger cited the continuing lack of advertiser
support as the reason for closing the magazine. The last issue will
be dated June/July. By Alex Kuczynski.
</P>
<P>
   (Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET.)
</P>
<P>
   (Bottom)
</P>
<P>
   REBOUND-NORRIS-COLUMN (Undated) _ The money managers panicked.
The people bought. That is the real story of the wild month that
ends Friday. After the worst week in Nasdaq history ended two weeks
ago, Wall Street braced for a wave of selling that did not arrive.
Instead, there was a rebound. That has happened time and again in
recent years.
</P>
