<HEADER>
A9164 &Cx1f; ttx-z
r s BC-RAC-BARNS-TEX     04-27 0434
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-RAC-BARNS-TEX </SLUG>
 
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TIM PRICE 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   GRAND PRAIRIE, Texas _ It sounds like one of those questions
that has an obvious answer. ``What makes a good barn?''
</P>
<P>
   Good horses, right?
</P>
<P>
   Whether or not a trainer has fast horses in his barn, there are
other things he's hoping for when a trainer comes for the racing
season at Lone Star Park at Grand Prairie.
</P>
<P>
   ``Vicinity to the racing surface,'' trainer Bob Young said.
``How cool are the barns, because some barns can get as hot as an
oven during the summer.''
</P>
<P>
   There are 29 barns at Lone Star, and they're located on the
northeast side of the property beyond the seven-furlong chute of
the racing surface.
</P>
<P>
   Young, a native of San Antonio, is stabled in Barn 16. As for
his concerns about vicinity to the racing surface, Young is about
in the middle of the barn area.
</P>
<P>
   The racing stables that enter the most horses or win the most
races tend to get closer to the racetrack. When trainer D. Wayne
Lukas moves his horses to Churchill Downs or Belmont Park, he's in
one of the closest barns to the track.
</P>
<P>
   At Lone Star Park, trainers Ronnie Werner and Gerald Romero are
stabled in barns adjacent to the track. Werner trains horses owned
by Tom Durant, a prominent car dealer from Grapevine who set a Lone
Star Park single-season record last year when he raced 80 horses.
Romero trains for Corsicana-based horse owners Leland and Sue Cook,
and they were the leading owners in races won last year.
</P>
<P>
   Leading trainer Steve Asmussen, however, takes a barn five spots
back.
</P>
<P>
   Wherever it's located, the barn serves as a locker room for each
trainer's stable, or team of horses. It's where the horses are fed,
bathed, groomed and given medical treatment. The horses live there
until the racing season is done.
</P>
<P>
   The trainer also keeps an office in his barn. Sometimes he makes
arrangements to rotate horses from an off-site training facility or
from other tracks. For example, Asmussen's family has a training
center located near Laredo. He also keeps horses at Churchill Downs
during the summer.
</P>
<P>
   With the amount of activity, and because the floors are dirt the
barn area can get quite filthy. Young said he makes an extra effort
to keep his place clean. The floors are raked, and tools are put
away after training hours. Some trainers, Young included, even
plant flowers outside the barn.
</P>
<P>
   ``You may not have good stock,'' Young said, ``but it doesn't
have to look like it. Keeping the barn clean is very important. I
think it depicts how you treat your stock.''
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
