of the 2000 Shell Houston Open PGA golf tournament being played at
the TPC course at The Woodlands. By EDDIE SEFKO.
</P>
<P>
   With: GLF-LOPEZ-COLUMN
</P>
<P>
   BBN-ASTROS (Houston) _ Pitcher Jose Lima fails to snap his
losing streak as the Chicago Cubs pound the Houston Astros 12-3 at
Enron Field. By JOSEPH DUARTE.
</P>
<P>
   With: BBN-ROBERTSON-COLUMN
</P>
<P>
   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ Gov. George W. Bush's new pitch for
more civilized politics strikes a welcome chord. But his words ring
hollow. He's already earned a reputation as a dirty street fighter,
trashing opponents and distorting their records. It's a stretch to
believe he intends to follow his own advice, change his stripes,
modify his intense partisanship and lighten up. By MARIANNE MEANS.
(Already filed.)
</P>
