<HEADLINE>
CATALANOTTO, MUNOZ EXAMINED
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By T.R. SULLIVAN 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   ARLINGTON, Texas _ Injured infielder Frank Catalanotto and
pitcher Mike Munoz were both examined by Dr. John Conway yesterday.
</P>
<P>
   Catalanotto, placed on the disabled list Saturday, is still
bothered by what Conway said was a ``severe tear'' of the groin
muscle. Catalanotto is expected to miss at least two more weeks.
</P>
<P>
   Munoz, after undergoing an MRI, has been diagnosed with chronic
tendinitis and was given a cortisone shot. He was placed on the
disabled list Wednesday and is expected to miss two weeks.  &QL; 
Rangers vs. Orioles
</P>
<P>
   The Rangers open a three-game series with the Baltimore Orioles
tonight at Camden Yards.
</P>
<P>
   The Rangers were 6-6 against the Orioles last season, going 3-3
against them at Camden Yards. The Orioles scored 81 runs against
the Rangers, the most by any opponent. Rangers pitchers allowed 20
home runs, 138 hits and 45 walks, all the most against any club.
Rafael Palmeiro hit .372 against the Orioles while Royce Clayton
hit .345, his second best against any American League team.
</P>
<P>
   The Orioles have considered activating right-hander Scott
Erickson off the disabled list and let him pitch Sunday against the
Rangers. But there are concerns about his velocity, and it's likely
they'll keep him on medical rehabilitation assignment for at least
one more start.
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
