<HEADLINE>
N.Y. TIMES NAMES NEW HEAD OF BROADCAST GROUP 
</HEADLINE>
   c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Cynthia H. Augustine, senior vice president for human
resources at The New York Times Co., will succeed C. Frank Roberts
as president of the broadcast group, the company announced on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   Until he retires at the end of the year, Roberts will become
chairman of the broadcast group, which includes eight
network-affiliated television stations and two New York City radio
stations. In her new role, Augustine, 42, will report to Roberts.
She will also retain her current title and responsibilities in
human resources.
</P>
<P>
   Augustine rejoined the Times Co. in that position in February
1998 from the law firm of Sabin, Bermant &AMP; Gould, where she was a
partner and specialized in employment law.
</P>
<P>
   She was a lawyer in the Times Co.'s legal department from 1986
to 1993. &QL;
</P>
