<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-NJ-BODY-FOUND-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
BODY FOUND IN SWAMP THOUGHT TO BE THAT OF KIDNAPPED MAN 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (ATTN: Ky.)   By ANDY NEWMAN   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   A body believed to be that of a 28-year-old British computer
consultant who had been kidnapped from his Kentucky hotel room 10
days ago was found half-buried in a swamp in Ocean County, N.J., on
Thursday, the FBI said.
</P>
<P>
   A New Jersey man who is suspected of posing as an FBI agent and
kidnapping the British man is being investigated in connection with
the death, the authorities said.
</P>
<P>
   The authorities said they believed that the New Jersey man,
Gregory J. Marcinski, 23, of Brick Township in Ocean County, might
have kidnapped the consultant, Paul Jeffrey Gale, because Gale was
dating Marcinski's former girlfriend.
</P>
<P>
   The body, which was awaiting positive identification on Thursday
night, was found near Marcinski's home, said Garey S. Chin, the
assistant agent in charge at the FBI's Newark, N.J., office.
</P>
<P>
   Marks on the body indicated the man had been strangled and
burned, the authorities said. It was unclear when the man had died
or how long the body had been in the swamp.
</P>
<P>
   On April 17 at 12:30 a.m., the authorities said, Marcinski,
posing as an FBI agent, went to the Holiday Inn in Florence, Ky., a
suburb of Cincinnati, where Gale was staying, woke him up and led
him to a car in the parking lot.
</P>
<P>
   A witness saw Gale being handcuffed and getting into the
passenger seat, the agency said. It was the last time Gale, a
programmer who was in Kentucky working as a consultant in the
merger of two pharmaceutical companies, was seen alive.
</P>
<P>
   Later that day, Marcinski returned to New Jersey, showed his
housemate, Preston C. Foray Jr., the body in the trunk of his car,
and asked for help burying it, said Special Agent Sandra Carroll, a
spokeswoman for the agency.
</P>
<P>
   Foray, 22, has been charged with being an accessory after the
fact to the kidnapping, Chin said.
</P>
<P>
   Marcinski was arrested on April 19 in Red Bank, N.J., and
charged with impersonating an FBI agent and has been held at the
Monmouth County jail since then. He is also awaiting extradition to
Kentucky on kidnapping charges.
</P>
<P>
   On Thursday about 2 a.m., Chin said, investigators went to a
marshy area in Brick and found a shirtless body with strangulation
marks on the neck and burn marks from a flammable liquid. Chin said
the killer might have wanted to burn the body to destroy evidence.
</P>
<P>
   If Marcinski is charged with murder, whether he is charged in
Kentucky, New Jersey or elsewhere will depend on where Gale is
determined to have been murdered.
</P>
<P>
   Chin said that the authorities believed that Marcinski killed
Gale in Kentucky and drove the 800 miles back to New Jersey with
the body in the car, his grandmother's Buick.
</P>
<P>
   Gale had recently lived in Mount Laurel, N.J., where he worked
for TRW Integrated Supply, Chin said. He was dating a former
girlfriend of Marcinski's, the authorities said, who had a
restraining order against Marcinski.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-04-27-00 2344EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
